creator: balexander@informative.com
text:
I installed JK-1.2.13, then realized I really needed JK-1.2.10.  I tried
installing JK-1.2.10.  It said can't install older version over newer (fair
enough). I then un-installed JK-1.2.13, and installed JK-1.2.10.  Same result! 
In order to accomplish what I wanted I had to use regedit to get rid of the
numerous registry entries that were not cleaned up by the JK-1.2.13 installation.

Before unistall you need to stop the IIS.
Anyhow, unexpected results could happen when doing such
things with original Microsoft applications like a simple Office,
so AFICT we are fine :)
